parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distance, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
grinding noise when braking
extended stopping distance
vehicle skids
brake pedal sinks to the floor
and vehicle shakes from side to side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent brake problem can cause the brakes to fail unexpectedly, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brakes fail to respond
the brake pedal sinks to the floor
and the vehicle experiences extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Frame Corrosion and Suspension Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the rear frame and suspension components can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rear suspension components breaking off
loss of vehicle control
loud noises
and difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Notification and Inadequate Recall Response
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to notify vehicle owners of recalls and inadequate response to recall notices can lead to continued operation of unsafe vehicles, potentially causing accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Owners not receiving recall notices
dealerships refusing to repair recalled vehicles
and inadequate response from manufacturers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and structural failure of the frame can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The frame is corroded and deteriorated
the rear sway bars separate from the subframe
the rear passenger side strut separates from the subframe
the rear tail arm bracket breaks off
the center cross member and rear frame are completely rusted
the frame exhibits severe rust and breaks in half.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shrinkage of the soft top convertible can cause fumes to enter the vehicle, potentially leading to carbon monoxide poisoning.
symptoms: The soft top convertible shrinks during hot summer weather
allowing fumes to enter the vehicle
carbon monoxide comes through the cracks.
